.so ../sci.an
.SH NAME
full -  sparse to full matrix conversion
.SH CALING SEQUENCE
.nf
X=full(sp)
.fi
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
sp
: real or complex sparse (or full) matrix
.TP
X
: full matrix
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fVX=full(sp)\fR converts the sparse matrix \fVsp\fR into its
full representation. (If \fVsp\fR is already full then \fVX\fR equals
\fVsp\fR).
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
sp=sparse([1,2;5,4;3,1],[1,2,3]);
A=full(sp)
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
sparse, sprand, speye

                        
